HEADWORD: Resaw
<hw>Re*saw"</hw> <pr>(r<?/-s<?/")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To saw
again; specifically, to saw a balk, or a timber, which has already been
squared, into dimension lumber, as joists, boards, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

